# Real-Time Face Recognition System

A production-quality real-time face recognition application built on
**face_recognition** (dlib) and **OpenCV**, with a clean CLI and
interactive webcam enrollment.

---

## Features

| Feature | Details |
|---|---|
| Live recognition | Webcam stream annotated in real time |
| Multi-face | Detects and recognises any number of faces per frame |
| Confidence scores | Visual indicator (green → cyan → red) |
| Enrollment | Via webcam (5 samples) or static image |
| CLI | `run` · `enroll` · `list` · `remove` |
| In-app hotkeys | `E` enroll · `I` image-enroll · `L` list · `R` remove · `S` screenshot |
| Persistence | Pickle database, survives restarts |
| Frame skipping | Configurable – keeps display smooth on CPU-only machines |
| Downscaling | Optional 0.5× pre-scale for faster detection |

---

## Requirements

```
Python 3.9+
cmake, dlib build tools
```

### macOS
```bash
brew install cmake dlib
```

### Ubuntu / Debian
```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y cmake libopenblas-dev liblapack-dev libx11-dev
```

### Windows
Install [Visual Studio Build Tools](https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/) (C++ workload), then:
```
pip install cmake dlib
```

---

## Installation

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
cd face_recognition_system
python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate   # Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Start live recognition (press E to enroll the first person)
python main.py run

# 2. Enroll from a photo
python main.py enroll "Alice" --image alice.jpg

# 3. Check who is enrolled
python main.py list

# 4. Remove someone
python main.py remove "Alice"
```

---

## Live Controls

| Key | Action |
|---|---|
| `Q` / `Esc` | Quit |
| `E` | Enroll new face via webcam |
| `I` | Enroll from image file |
| `L` | List database in terminal |
| `R` | Remove identity |
| `S` | Save screenshot |

---

## Configuration

Edit `src/config.py` to tune:

| Parameter | Default | Effect |
|---|---|---|
| `tolerance` | `0.50` | Lower = stricter matching |
| `detection_model` | `"hog"` | `"cnn"` is more accurate (needs GPU) |
| `scale_factor` | `0.50` | Smaller = faster, misses small faces |
| `frame_skip` | `2` | Recognise every Nth frame |
| `enrollment_samples` | `5` | Samples collected during webcam enroll |

---

## Project Layout

```
face_recognition_system/
├── main.py               ← Entry point + CLI
├── requirements.txt
├── README.md
└── src/
    ├── config.py         ← All tunable parameters
    ├── database.py       ← Pickle-based face store
    ├── recognizer.py     ← Detection · matching · drawing
    ├── camera.py         ← OpenCV capture wrapper
    ├── enrollment.py     ← Webcam enrollment state machine
    └── utils.py          ← Rich terminal helpers
```

---

## Performance Tips

- Use `--model hog` (default) on CPU; switch to `--model cnn` with a CUDA GPU.
- Lower `scale_factor` to `0.25` and raise `frame_skip` to `3–4` on slow hardware.
- Increase `enrollment_samples` (10–15) and `num_jitters` (5–10) for better accuracy.

